opps: object oriented programing

CLASS:
->class is a collection of different different data members

->class is a collection of elements
->class is a user difined data type

syntax:
class <class name>
{
    public:
    data members;
    members function();
};
----------------------------
OBJECT:
->object is a instance of class or we can say thet object is a variable of class

->using of object we can access properties of class

syntex:
classname object=classname();
------------------------------
